  "text": "The implementation of crd_client.go follows the established patterns from the Kubernetes client-go codebase for typed resource clients. The key pattern source files are: kubernetes/typed/core/v1/configmap.go and kubernetes/typed/core/v1/namespace.go, which demonstrate the standard interface and implementation structure for resource clients. The ConfigMapInterface defines the contract with Create, Get, List, and Delete methods that accept context.Context and appropriate metav1 options. The client implementation uses the rest.Interface from rest/client.go to build HTTP requests through a fluent request builder pattern (Get().Namespace().Resource().Name().Do().Into()). The kubernetes/typed/core/v1/core_client.go file provides the pattern for the group client (ExampleV1Client), including the RESTClient() method that returns rest.Interface, the setConfigDefaults() function that configures the GroupVersion and APIPath for the API group, and factory functions (NewForConfig, NewForConfigAndClient, New) for client instantiation. The gentype/type.go file illustrates the underlying implementation details of Create (using Post()), Get, List, and Delete operations that chain method calls on the REST client. All methods follow the Kubernetes client-go convention of accepting context.Context as the first parameter after the receiver, enabling proper context propagation for cancellation and timeouts. The Widget custom resource is defined with TypeMeta and ObjectMeta (via embedding) and implements the runtime.Object interface through DeepCopyObject methods, matching the pattern expected by rest.Interface for serialization and deserialization."
